      "id": "498",
      "title": "Which was the first person who informed Hazrat Ayesha (RA) about the eveent of Afak?",
      "answer": "Hazrat Ummay Mustah bin Asasah (RA)",
      "explanation": "<div class=\"explanation-body\">\n\n<p><font style=\"background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\"><span style=\"font-family: Helvetica;\"><font color=\"#0000ff\">The first person who </font><font color=\"#00ff00\">informed</font><font color=\"#0000ff\"> Hazrat Ayesha (RA) about the slander (known as the Event of Ifk) was </font><font color=\"#ff0000\">Umm Mistah bint Abi Ruhm. </font></span></font></p><p><font style=\"\"><span style=\"font-family: Helvetica;\"><font color=\"#0000ff\" style=\"background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\"> incident occurred</font><font color=\"#00ff00\" style=\"background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\"> during a period</font><font color=\"#0000ff\" style=\"background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\"> when Hazrat Ayesha (RA) was left behind on </font><font color=\"#ff0000\" style=\"background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\">an expedition and later accused of infidelity. </font></span></font></p><p><font color=\"#0000ff\" style=\"background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\"><br/></font></p><p><font color=\"#0000ff\" style=\"background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\"><br/></font></p><p><font color=\"#0000ff\" style=\"background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\"><br/></font></p><p><font color=\"#0000ff\" style=\"background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\"><br/></font></p><p><font color=\"#0000ff\" style=\"background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\"><br/></font></p><p><br/></p>\n</div>"
    },
    {
      "id": "499",
      "title": "The Hadith book in which all the Hadith reported by a particular companion are compiled is called:",
      "answer": "Mustadrak",
      "explanation": "<div class=\"explanation-body\">\n\n<ul><li><font face=\"Arial\"><b style=\"\"><span style=\"font-family: Tahoma;\"><span style=\"color: rgb(0, 0, 255);\">The Hadith book in which all the Hadith reported by a particular companion are compiled is called </span><span style=\"color: rgb(255, 0, 0); background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\">Mustadrak</span></span></b></font></li><li><font color=\"#0000ff\" face=\"Arial\"><b><span style=\"font-family: Tahoma;\">**</span></b></font><span style=\"background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\"><br/></span></li><li><b><span style=\"background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\"><span style=\"font-family: Tahoma; color: rgb(0, 0, 255);\">Al-</span><span style=\"font-family: Tahoma; color: rgb(0, 0, 255);\">Mustadrak 'ala al-Sahihayn</span><span style=\"font-family: Tahoma; color: rgb(0, 0, 255);\"> </span></span><span style=\"font-family: Arial; color: rgb(0, 0, 255);\"><span style=\"background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); font-family: Tahoma;\">كم</span><span style=\"font-family: Tahoma;\">) is a five-volume </span></span><span style=\"font-family: Tahoma; color: rgb(255, 0, 0);\">hadith collection</span><span style=\"font-family: Tahoma; color: rgb(0, 0, 255);\"> written by Hakim al-Nishapuri (Nishapur is located in Iran). </span></b></li><li><b><span style=\"font-family: Tahoma; color: rgb(0, 0, 255);\">He wrote it in the </span><span style=\"color: rgb(255, 0, 0); background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\"><span style=\"font-family: Tahoma;\">year AH 393 (1002–1003 CE)</span><span style=\"font-family: Tahoma;\">,</span></span><span style=\"font-family: Tahoma; color: rgb(0, 0, 255);\"> when he was </span><span style=\"color: rgb(255, 0, 0); background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\"><span style=\"font-family: Tahoma;\">72 years old</span><span style=\"font-family: Tahoma;\">. </span></span></b></li><li><span style=\"font-family: Arial; font-weight: bold; font-size: 1rem;\"><span style=\"color: rgb(255, 0, 0); font-family: Tahoma;\">Mustadraks</span><span style=\"font-family: Tahoma;\"> </span><span style=\"color: rgb(0, 0, 255); font-family: Tahoma;\">have been authored for various subjects such as Jurisprudence, Rijal, Hadith etc</span></span></li></ul>\n</div>"
    },
    {
      "id": "500",
      "title": "What was the name of the wife of Pharaoh who believed in Prophet Musa (AS)?",
      "answer": "Asiya",
      "explanation": "<div class=\"explanation-body\">\n\n<p><b><font color=\"#ff0000\">Asiya</font><font color=\"#0000ff\">, the wife of </font><font color=\"#ff0000\">Pharaoh</font><font color=\"#0000ff\">, is honored in Islam for her </font><font color=\"#ff0000\">strong faith</font><font color=\"#0000ff\"> in Allah despite her husband's tyranny.</font></b></p><p><b><font color=\"#0000ff\">She protected </font><font color=\"#ff0000\">baby Musa (AS)</font><font color=\"#0000ff\">.</font></b></p><p><b><font color=\"#0000ff\">She is considered one of the </font><font color=\"#ff0000\">four greatest women</font><font color=\"#0000ff\"> in Islam.</font></b></p>\n</div>"
